<br>
<br>
and to this &quot; ALL my major works are done by copying photos and reference pics&quot; If you enjoy doing it, don't stop because of what someone said about it. It might as well just be your style. Besides, if everyone did that, we'd all be cavemen still because of all the inventions/discoveries there is bound to be someone that opposed. Most people and artists do copy from reference, and most the time its because the audience likes that stuff. But really I think it isn't what the artist really wants to do, take my art teacher for example, he paints so he can sell his paintings at an auction/sale , not for the fun of painting.Don't get me wrong, I'm sure someone out there enjoys painting AND sells them, but most the time when someone takes it too serious and bases his/her career on it , it takes all the enjoyment out of it.<br>
